WEBVTT

00:01.958 --> 00:03.829
Your Grace, Cardinal Wolsey

00:03.960 --> 00:05.135
has been speaking
with your daughter.

00:05.266 --> 00:06.919
He says she is to marry.

00:07.050 --> 00:08.225
[Catherine] Wolsey seeks
to wed her to the dauphin.

00:08.356 --> 00:09.574
I would sooner see her
marry Charles,

00:09.705 --> 00:11.272
the King of Spain.

00:11.359 --> 00:13.013
He is still kind to you?

00:13.143 --> 00:14.057
[Catherine]
He is changed.

00:14.188 --> 00:15.928
-I have given him nothing.
-Mary...

00:16.016 --> 00:18.540
she will be the one to rule
and follow you in greatness.

00:18.627 --> 00:21.064
[Lina]
We are being threatened.

00:21.195 --> 00:22.196
[Oviedo] I see the rioters
and the immigrants.

00:22.326 --> 00:24.067
-Henry, no!
-[blade plunges]

00:24.198 --> 00:25.634
It is the king who is the cause
of all their suffering.

00:25.764 --> 00:27.679
My sister Meg writes to me,

00:27.810 --> 00:30.117
claiming that her own marriage
is invalid.

00:30.204 --> 00:31.727
I know your family
has connections with the pope.

00:31.857 --> 00:34.121
Put to him my case
for an annulment.

00:34.251 --> 00:36.340
The man they call
the "Alter Rex,"

00:36.471 --> 00:38.212
the "other king."

00:38.299 --> 00:39.517
Catherine, go to Mary and tell
her she will be queen--

00:39.648 --> 00:41.128
Queen of Spain.

00:41.258 --> 00:42.999
Henry,
I am with child again.

00:43.130 --> 00:44.435
It's one final chance.

00:46.002 --> 00:48.700
[dramatic orchestral music]

00:48.874 --> 00:51.660
♪

01:35.095 --> 01:37.880
[bell tolling]

01:40.056 --> 01:42.798
[somber vocalization]

01:42.885 --> 01:45.757
♪

01:54.288 --> 01:56.116
[man grunts]

01:56.246 --> 01:57.639
[Catherine]
I fight.

01:57.769 --> 01:59.641
You fight.

01:59.771 --> 02:01.904
He fights.

02:02.034 --> 02:04.428
[unsettling ambient music]

02:04.559 --> 02:06.474
Pugno...

02:06.604 --> 02:08.563
pugnas, pugnat.

02:08.693 --> 02:10.042
[Catherine exhales softly]

02:10.173 --> 02:11.827
We fight.

02:11.957 --> 02:13.785
Come on at me, then,
if ya dare,

02:13.916 --> 02:15.483
ya Scots dog.

02:15.570 --> 02:17.180
Ah!

02:17.267 --> 02:18.573
[grunts]

02:18.703 --> 02:20.140
[Mary]
We fight.

02:21.228 --> 02:22.664
Pugnamus,

02:22.751 --> 02:24.100
pugnatis,

02:24.231 --> 02:26.450
pugnant.

02:26.581 --> 02:27.712
[wooden swords clacking]

02:27.843 --> 02:29.845
[Jamie grunting]

02:29.975 --> 02:31.542
You're dead, sassenach.

02:33.805 --> 02:35.633
[soldier] Arrest them!
Seize all the documents!

02:35.764 --> 02:38.419
[dramatic music]

02:38.593 --> 02:41.509
♪

02:41.639 --> 02:44.294
[people shouting indistinctly]

02:44.468 --> 02:46.949
♪

02:54.348 --> 02:55.566
Now, Mary, we will show
your father--

02:55.697 --> 02:58.003
No, no.
I-I need hear no more.

02:58.134 --> 03:01.224
Princess Mary is a wonderful
student, Your Majesty,

03:01.355 --> 03:02.747
a natural scholar.

03:02.878 --> 03:04.401
Girls can learn
as well as boys.

03:04.532 --> 03:05.968
To read the Gospels.

03:06.098 --> 03:08.057
[Catherine]
And even to govern.

03:11.278 --> 03:14.106
The queen has engaged
a tutor from Spain,

03:14.194 --> 03:16.065
Your Majesty.

03:16.196 --> 03:17.719
A remarkable-sounding man.

03:17.849 --> 03:19.851
Oh, very well.

03:19.982 --> 03:22.332
But as to who will govern
England after me,

03:22.463 --> 03:26.858
the answer does not lie
in here...

03:26.989 --> 03:29.600
but in there.

03:29.687 --> 03:31.167
[doors open]

03:31.298 --> 03:33.691
Your Majesty.

03:33.822 --> 03:35.954
The arrests have been made
in Blackfriars.

03:36.085 --> 03:37.347
Mm.

03:37.434 --> 03:38.566
What matter is this,
Lord Stafford?

03:38.696 --> 03:41.264
Ah, heretics, Your Grace,

03:41.351 --> 03:42.483
that started out of Saxony.

03:42.613 --> 03:44.224
Ah.

03:44.354 --> 03:46.574
Martin Luther's reformists.

03:46.704 --> 03:48.228
They say the pope is not holy

03:48.315 --> 03:49.794
and the king
is not anointed by God.

03:49.925 --> 03:51.405
[Stafford]
Indeed, Your Grace.

03:51.535 --> 03:53.363
Oh, and, Your Majesty,

03:53.494 --> 03:56.540
that milksop from Scotland
requests audience.

03:56.671 --> 03:58.107
[Henry groans softly]

03:58.194 --> 04:00.283
We were going after deer.

04:02.329 --> 04:04.374
[footsteps departing]

04:04.505 --> 04:06.071
[doors close]

04:06.158 --> 04:08.117
You did very well, Mary.

04:08.248 --> 04:11.468
She would have done better with
a stronger governess, perhaps.

04:11.599 --> 04:14.384
You have indulged her
too often, Maggie.

04:14.515 --> 04:16.168
[Albany]
There were several dispatches

04:16.299 --> 04:18.083
from the Holy Father,
Your Grace,

04:18.214 --> 04:20.477
but, uh, nothing about
an annulment of your marriage.

04:20.608 --> 04:22.784
[huffs] When will this be
at an end?

04:22.914 --> 04:26.004
-[sighs]
-Mm. It gets worse.

04:26.135 --> 04:27.397
We've just learned
Angus has ridden

04:27.484 --> 04:30.008
to London to petition
the king for support.

04:30.095 --> 04:32.533
By Christ Jesu.

04:32.663 --> 04:35.492
What is marriage
but a chain around the body,

04:35.579 --> 04:37.233
pulling you into the depths?

04:37.364 --> 04:39.409
I need independence,

04:39.540 --> 04:41.846
and my brother denies me
my inheritance!

04:41.977 --> 04:43.935
This money from your brother
is a phantom, Your Grace.

04:44.066 --> 04:45.197
You must let it go.

04:45.328 --> 04:46.503
No.

04:46.590 --> 04:48.200
[sighs]

04:48.288 --> 04:50.855
I will go to London
and speak to my brother.

04:50.986 --> 04:52.727
What about that cur, Angus?

04:52.857 --> 04:55.077
If I see him,
I will cut his manhood off.

04:55.164 --> 04:57.209
Hal Stewart!

04:57.297 --> 04:59.473
Ready my horses and provisions.

04:59.603 --> 05:02.127
We have a long ride ahead.

05:02.258 --> 05:03.433
[Angus]
My wife

05:03.520 --> 05:06.741
divides kingdoms
with her arrogance.

05:06.871 --> 05:08.960
She creates bad humor
within our land.

05:10.962 --> 05:13.313
She's openly hostile
towards you, Your Grace.

05:15.140 --> 05:17.447
Your Majesty,

05:17.534 --> 05:19.275
Margaret may even incite
more violence

05:19.406 --> 05:21.059
against the English.

05:21.190 --> 05:23.627
[Catherine]
Your Majesty...

05:23.714 --> 05:25.977
Meg doesn't want a war.

05:26.108 --> 05:27.370
The earl has
personal grievances

05:27.501 --> 05:29.503
which he attempts
to drag you into.

05:29.633 --> 05:31.766
She asked the pope
to annul our union,

05:31.896 --> 05:33.768
to declare
our marriage illegitimate.

05:33.898 --> 05:35.639
I forbade her
this course of action.

05:35.770 --> 05:37.249
-She makes a fool of me.
-This plan is futile.

05:37.380 --> 05:39.339
Indeed.

05:39.426 --> 05:42.124
A marriage made in God's eyes
cannot be undone.

05:44.387 --> 05:45.910
Unless the pope decides it.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.915
All things are possible
from Rome.

05:54.745 --> 05:57.748
This fool is ill news,
Your Majesty.

05:57.879 --> 05:59.750
He upsets the prince.

05:59.837 --> 06:01.578
Ride back to Scotland, Angus.

06:01.709 --> 06:03.624
-I-I merely warn you to--
-No.

06:03.754 --> 06:07.671
You're dismissed, my lord.

06:07.758 --> 06:11.109
[bell tolling in the distance]

06:11.240 --> 06:13.938
[door opens]

06:14.069 --> 06:15.853
Such talk of waging war
on the sanctity of marriage.

06:15.984 --> 06:17.594
-[door closes]
-That this could even be raised

06:17.725 --> 06:18.987
to pollute this court...

06:19.117 --> 06:20.162
[Wolsey]
And the church digs them out.

06:20.249 --> 06:21.468
Undersheriff More
has been charged

06:21.598 --> 06:22.991
with finding the ringleaders.

06:23.121 --> 06:26.386
And I pray
that every rat is caught...

06:26.516 --> 06:27.996
in the name of God

06:28.126 --> 06:30.825
and in the name
of God's appointed king.

06:30.955 --> 06:33.654
[dramatic music]

06:33.828 --> 06:36.657
♪

06:42.314 --> 06:44.012
[bell tolls in the distance]

06:50.584 --> 06:52.368
[Catherine]
Earl Angus,

06:52.499 --> 06:54.370
we understand
that the Duke of Albany

06:54.501 --> 06:55.980
proposes a petition
to the pope

06:56.111 --> 06:57.634
for your marriage
to be annulled.

06:57.765 --> 07:00.332
Yes, eh, he does.
As Meg's co-regent, he--

07:00.463 --> 07:02.465
[Catherine]
Is that all he is?

07:02.596 --> 07:05.076
Co-regent?

07:05.207 --> 07:07.035
If they were lovers,

07:07.165 --> 07:10.647
the pope would see they had
a personal and immoral motive

07:10.778 --> 07:13.041
and throw out their petition
without consideration.

07:13.171 --> 07:14.477
[Angus chuckles]

07:14.608 --> 07:16.827
I see, Your Grace.

07:16.958 --> 07:19.047
Yes, that would be so.

07:19.177 --> 07:20.265
I will inform
the Scottish council.

07:20.396 --> 07:22.267
Waste no time.

07:22.398 --> 07:23.747
Return to Edinburgh

07:23.878 --> 07:26.620
and tell them
of the queen's disgrace.

07:26.750 --> 07:29.405
You have our support.

07:29.536 --> 07:32.321
[dark music]

07:32.408 --> 07:35.498
♪

07:35.629 --> 07:38.283
[indistinct chatter]

07:38.458 --> 07:41.330
♪

07:44.551 --> 07:47.249
-[man] Bloody foreigners.
-[man 2] That's right.

07:47.379 --> 07:52.036
An army
is for a valiant purpose...

07:52.167 --> 07:55.736
for war,
for the upkeep of justice.

07:58.216 --> 08:01.655
More and more,
I feel like a street thug.

08:01.785 --> 08:03.526
[Lina sighs]

08:05.223 --> 08:07.095
There is a darkness at court.

08:09.706 --> 08:12.840
The king prowls the palace,

08:12.970 --> 08:16.800
and the queen
looks for his favor.

08:16.931 --> 08:20.761
She seems
ever more desperate.

08:20.891 --> 08:24.155
It no longer feels safe
anywhere, Ovideo,

08:24.286 --> 08:26.157
even here at home.

08:27.550 --> 08:29.509
This is a different England.

08:29.639 --> 08:31.728
[baby fusses]

08:31.902 --> 08:34.992
♪

08:35.123 --> 08:37.386
[baby continues fussing]

08:38.996 --> 08:40.824
Lord, You have taken
all my sons.

08:40.955 --> 08:43.087
[breathes deeply]

08:43.218 --> 08:45.655
Is not the price
of my sin paid?

08:45.786 --> 08:48.266
[softly]
Please.

08:48.353 --> 08:50.312
Please grant me a boy.

08:54.098 --> 08:55.796
[normal voice]
I will prove my worth, Lord.

08:57.449 --> 08:59.974
I will defend Your church.

09:00.104 --> 09:02.672
I will please both You
and Your anointed king...

09:02.803 --> 09:05.022
[footsteps approach]

09:05.153 --> 09:06.937
What do you want?

09:07.068 --> 09:08.722
[Wolsey] If I may be so bold,
Your Grace,

09:08.809 --> 09:12.203
what a strange thing to ask
a cardinal in a church.

09:12.334 --> 09:14.118
[chuckles]

09:16.860 --> 09:21.473
The king's sister Margaret
rides south towards court.

09:21.604 --> 09:24.738
We hope you can reason
with her.

09:24.825 --> 09:26.870
[Catherine]
I have loved her well,

09:26.957 --> 09:28.655
but she goes too far
with talk of annulment.

09:28.742 --> 09:30.961
[Wolsey]
Mm.

09:33.834 --> 09:35.052
Where, uh...

09:36.619 --> 09:38.186
Where are your ladies?

09:39.970 --> 09:42.364
I wish to walk alone.

09:42.494 --> 09:44.366
I notice you walk alone
more often.

09:44.496 --> 09:46.977
I pray alone.

09:47.108 --> 09:49.327
-For the heir.
-[Wolsey] Mm.

09:49.414 --> 09:52.853
Must require a great deal
of supplication...

09:52.983 --> 09:57.422
to maintain such faith
in the wake of...

09:57.509 --> 09:59.294
so much loss.

09:59.381 --> 10:01.731
[scoffs]

10:01.862 --> 10:04.647
Yes.

10:04.778 --> 10:06.780
And now
my son and I will retire.

10:08.999 --> 10:11.262
It is a threat, Wolsey.

10:13.090 --> 10:15.310
This Protestant heresy.

10:17.138 --> 10:19.531
We both feel it.

10:19.662 --> 10:21.751
So perhaps we should stop
bickering between ourselves

10:21.882 --> 10:25.015
and defend our God
and our king...

10:25.102 --> 10:27.148
for both our sakes.

10:29.367 --> 10:31.108
What do you say?

10:31.239 --> 10:33.937
[disquieting music]

10:34.024 --> 10:36.853
♪

10:38.986 --> 10:42.206
[bell tolling]

10:44.382 --> 10:46.907
Printed upon London presses

10:47.037 --> 10:48.909
and sent all over the country.

10:49.039 --> 10:50.998
And the hideous poison spreads.

10:51.128 --> 10:54.044
Now they say that the Church
cannot absolve sin

10:54.175 --> 10:56.786
and that giving alms
does not cleanse the soul.

10:56.917 --> 10:59.310
Then what do they think
Christ died for?

10:59.441 --> 11:01.617
-Sin can be washed away.
-[Wolsey] Hmm.

11:01.748 --> 11:03.575
We can be made clean again
by God's grace.

11:03.706 --> 11:05.316
The queen is quite correct,

11:05.447 --> 11:08.058
both in her disgust
at this filth

11:08.145 --> 11:10.670
but also in her ecumenical
argument against it.

11:10.800 --> 11:13.411
God be praised we destroyed
a press in Blackfriars.

11:13.498 --> 11:15.022
One press will not stop it.

11:15.152 --> 11:17.067
We have mustered men
from the palace barracks.

11:17.198 --> 11:19.679
Rest assured,
there'll be many more arrests.

11:19.766 --> 11:21.289
[Henry] Good.
The rats must be stamped out.

11:21.419 --> 11:23.421
Are we not in danger
of hysteria?

11:27.208 --> 11:27.991
[Brandon]
How so?

11:31.081 --> 11:34.694
This group of fanatics
is a tiny minority.

11:38.393 --> 11:40.525
A dangerous group, nonetheless.

11:40.656 --> 11:42.397
The king and queen are right

11:42.484 --> 11:43.833
to pronounce heresy
and treason.

11:43.964 --> 11:47.271
So we waste men

11:47.402 --> 11:49.447
and taxes
that our army needs--

11:49.534 --> 11:51.101
One spark can burn a city,
Lord Stafford!

11:53.190 --> 11:56.367
But instead, a fire
must be made of this filth,

11:56.498 --> 11:58.108
as the cardinal calls it.

11:58.239 --> 11:59.849
[Wolsey]
And if necessary,

11:59.936 --> 12:02.504
from those who spread it.

12:02.634 --> 12:04.419
Yes.

12:04.549 --> 12:05.899
If it should come to that.

12:07.944 --> 12:09.729
We are defending God,
gentlemen,

12:09.859 --> 12:11.469
and His King of England.

12:11.600 --> 12:13.080
-Hear, hear.
-Hear.

12:13.210 --> 12:15.691
Well, we'll think on it.

12:24.265 --> 12:28.182
[door opens, closes]

12:28.312 --> 12:31.925
Between you and Wolsey,
I'm surrounded by good counsel.

12:32.055 --> 12:34.318
I love that look in your eye
when your blood's up.

12:34.449 --> 12:35.885
Mm.

12:36.016 --> 12:38.627
It is the power
of the prince within me.

12:38.758 --> 12:41.586
He gives me his strength...

12:41.673 --> 12:43.414
which comes from you.

12:46.766 --> 12:48.550
Meg wishes to betray
her wedding vows

12:48.680 --> 12:51.509
at first sign of trouble.

12:51.640 --> 12:54.121
But we, Henry...

12:54.208 --> 12:58.212
we overcome
and find ourselves again.

12:58.342 --> 13:00.170
Do you hate my sister now?

13:00.301 --> 13:01.955
I hate her heresy.

13:03.826 --> 13:05.959
Annulment of marriage
will damn her soul.

13:06.089 --> 13:08.526
Then again,
if I just indulge her,

13:08.657 --> 13:10.180
then that might shut
her bleating.

13:10.311 --> 13:12.182
It's her own soul
she risks, not mine.

13:12.313 --> 13:13.140
[Catherine]
No...

13:14.924 --> 13:17.144
No, Henry, it is an outrage.

13:17.274 --> 13:19.407
If she pushes for this,
then Meg is possessed

13:19.537 --> 13:20.800
by the same devil that inspires
Martin Luther and his--

13:20.930 --> 13:22.279
[Henry]
Oh, oh. Shh.

13:22.410 --> 13:24.760
Stop.
You must not upset the baby.

13:24.891 --> 13:26.675
-It must be calm within you--
-H-he. He.

13:28.329 --> 13:30.113
It is a he, Henry.

13:32.333 --> 13:33.943
We are beloved.

13:34.030 --> 13:37.251
Well, if we are beloved,
then Stafford must be hated.

13:38.774 --> 13:41.342
The man has three sons.

13:41.472 --> 13:43.474
You saw what just happened.

13:43.605 --> 13:47.217
I'm questioned at counsel.

13:47.348 --> 13:50.830
If I had a son,
it would reassert my authority.

13:52.483 --> 13:54.746
Then I will hurry him to you.

13:54.834 --> 13:57.706
[sweeping music]

13:57.793 --> 14:00.665
♪

14:00.752 --> 14:02.972
[Hal]
Whoa, Grace, slow down.

14:03.146 --> 14:05.061
♪

14:05.192 --> 14:07.107
-Whoa, whoa.
-Ha.

14:07.237 --> 14:08.804
[panting]
What's wrong?

14:08.891 --> 14:10.675
We'll snap our horses
in two at this rate.

14:10.762 --> 14:12.199
[laughing]
Don't fret.

14:12.329 --> 14:14.070
I'm not some posy
of bonnie flowers, Hal Stewart.

14:14.201 --> 14:16.290
It's not ya I'm worried about.
It's me.

14:16.377 --> 14:17.639
-[laughs]
-I haven't ridden like that

14:17.769 --> 14:19.728
since racing my cousins
on the farm.

14:19.859 --> 14:21.817
Oh, so it's a race
you're after.

14:21.948 --> 14:23.427
[laughs]
That's not what I said.

14:25.342 --> 14:27.127
But a race to London it is.
Come on!

14:27.214 --> 14:29.564
-[grunts]
-Yah!

14:29.694 --> 14:32.045
Ha ha!
[laughing]

14:32.219 --> 14:35.048
♪

14:37.137 --> 14:38.834
[Catherine] Señor Vives
has traveled from Spain.

14:38.921 --> 14:40.270
-[Vives] Your Grace.
-[Catherine] All this way

14:40.401 --> 14:42.446
to teach you astronomy,
mathematics, poetry.

14:42.577 --> 14:44.013
[Vives]
Indeed.

14:44.144 --> 14:45.972
[Maggie] As Princess Mary's
governess, señor,

14:46.102 --> 14:49.410
I can attest
to her serious curiosity.

14:49.540 --> 14:51.586
But I would encourage you
to coax her to study

14:51.716 --> 14:53.414
and not to indulge her.

14:53.544 --> 14:55.633
Will you go to him now, Mary?

14:56.547 --> 14:58.680
[Lina]
Con rapidez,Princess Mary.

14:59.899 --> 15:02.379
[Mary giggling]

15:02.466 --> 15:04.338
[Vives]
Princess Mary.

15:04.468 --> 15:06.775
-Princess Mary.
-[woman] Princess Mary.

15:06.862 --> 15:08.429
[Vives]
Come back!

15:08.559 --> 15:11.127
She's--if you will permit me,
Highness... [chuckles]

15:11.214 --> 15:13.477
She is much as you were.

15:13.564 --> 15:15.827
She will be a fine companion
to the King of England.

15:15.958 --> 15:17.090
Her brother.

15:19.135 --> 15:20.876
[Maggie] As Princess Mary
is with Señor Vives,

15:21.007 --> 15:22.922
Your Grace,
may I be excused?

15:27.317 --> 15:30.059
We see so little
of you both these days.

15:30.190 --> 15:33.497
And Charlie was always
so close to the king.

15:33.628 --> 15:35.282
There was a time

15:35.412 --> 15:37.414
where Charlie wouldn't want
to be anywhere else

15:37.501 --> 15:39.286
other than at court, but...

15:40.765 --> 15:43.377
What do you mean?

15:43.507 --> 15:44.682
Is Charlie displeased
with the king?

15:44.813 --> 15:46.249
No, never!

15:46.380 --> 15:47.729
Never.

15:47.859 --> 15:51.472
He-he loves the king,
a-as I do,

15:51.602 --> 15:55.867
but there are others the king
looks to in his wisdom.

15:55.998 --> 15:57.739
As Lady Pole
looks to the wisdom

15:57.869 --> 16:01.438
of Thomas More, I notice,
a great deal.

16:01.569 --> 16:04.267
[indistinct chatter]

16:06.574 --> 16:08.924
[Wolsey] Lady Pole,
how fares your daughter

16:09.055 --> 16:10.926
and her new husband?

16:11.057 --> 16:12.972
They are well.
Thank you, Cardinal.

16:13.102 --> 16:14.712
I will see them soon
at Lord Stafford's estate,

16:14.843 --> 16:15.887
where they now have rooms.

16:16.018 --> 16:18.455
Ah, yes.

16:18.542 --> 16:20.066
The grand house.

16:20.196 --> 16:21.241
Hmm.

16:21.371 --> 16:24.026
Hopefully, a fine inheritance.

16:24.157 --> 16:27.421
It will be.
Most certainly.

16:27.551 --> 16:29.858
Why would "hopefully"
come into it?

16:31.338 --> 16:32.730
[Wolsey]
Thomas.

16:32.861 --> 16:33.644
[Henry Pole]
Let's move out!

16:33.775 --> 16:34.776
Move out!

16:36.778 --> 16:38.171
You may like to know

16:38.258 --> 16:39.911
that I have heard
from Reggie in Oxford.

16:40.042 --> 16:41.087
-Ah!
-He thrives.

16:41.217 --> 16:42.262
Good.

16:42.392 --> 16:43.654
I'm glad.

16:43.785 --> 16:45.047
And I feel foolish to ask

16:45.178 --> 16:48.529
for my other son, but...

16:48.616 --> 16:51.401
he is too zealous
in the name of the king.

16:51.532 --> 16:53.751
He gets so angry,

16:53.882 --> 16:57.233
and I'm sure that you could
cool the fire in his blood...

16:57.364 --> 16:59.105
[exhales sharply]

16:59.235 --> 17:01.629
Forgive me, I'm not quite
sure what I'm asking, but--

17:01.759 --> 17:04.414
I could assign him
to my personal guard.

17:04.545 --> 17:06.112
That way, I could keep
a watchful eye on him

17:06.242 --> 17:07.983
if need be.

17:08.114 --> 17:09.202
How does that sound?

17:09.332 --> 17:11.595
[exhales sharply]
Thank you.

17:11.726 --> 17:14.033
Thank you, Thomas.
You are...

17:14.163 --> 17:15.643
[inhales deeply,
exhales sharply]

17:15.773 --> 17:17.471
It is a dark world sometimes,

17:17.601 --> 17:20.213
but you are the candle
that is constant

17:20.300 --> 17:21.692
and never flickers.

17:21.823 --> 17:24.782
"Candle that is constant."
[laughs]

17:24.913 --> 17:27.350
You should be a writer.
[chuckles]

17:27.481 --> 17:31.006
Would you consider coming
to my family house in Chelsea?

17:31.137 --> 17:32.877
I have a wonderful
private study there

17:33.008 --> 17:35.228
where I also write and read,

17:35.358 --> 17:37.447
which I'd love
to share with you.

17:37.578 --> 17:38.840
Maybe even have
some lemon cake.

17:38.970 --> 17:40.798
[both chuckle]

17:40.929 --> 17:43.062
How does that sound?

17:43.192 --> 17:45.673
-That sounds wonderful.
-Good.

17:45.803 --> 17:48.589
[Maggie chuckles awkwardly]

17:48.719 --> 17:50.852
The world is a dark place,
Maggie,

17:50.982 --> 17:53.681
but my home is my haven.

17:53.811 --> 17:56.901
And, well...

17:57.032 --> 17:59.513
it would gladden my heart
if it became your haven, too.

18:01.036 --> 18:03.169
Do come.

18:03.299 --> 18:04.909
[bell tolls]

18:05.040 --> 18:06.607
[Wiltshire]
We took five men and women

18:06.737 --> 18:08.522
to the cells at Southwark.

18:08.652 --> 18:11.002
They were passing out
the same heretical writings.

18:14.267 --> 18:17.835
A public hanging would send
a clear message, Your Grace.

18:17.966 --> 18:22.231
For now, I believe heavy fines
will suffice, Your Grace.

18:22.362 --> 18:23.972
The king's divine station
is assaulted,

18:24.059 --> 18:25.452
and a fine is sufficient?

18:27.802 --> 18:31.066
Your Grace, the Church
petitions for swift justice.

18:35.723 --> 18:37.246
Collect
every disgusting pamphlet

18:37.377 --> 18:39.335
you can find, Wiltshire.

18:39.466 --> 18:41.163
The cardinal and I
will have a public burning,

18:41.294 --> 18:43.339
and the message
will be clear.

18:47.604 --> 18:50.346
We do not burn heretics
in England, Your Grace.

18:52.087 --> 18:54.045
I know.

18:54.176 --> 18:56.918
[dramatic music]

18:57.092 --> 18:59.921
♪

19:00.051 --> 19:02.750
[indistinct chatter]

19:02.924 --> 19:05.796
♪

19:14.065 --> 19:15.850
[Wiltshire]
Good people of London,

19:15.980 --> 19:17.678
His Majesty, King Henry,

19:17.808 --> 19:20.550
and his exalted Queen Catherine

19:20.637 --> 19:22.683
ask you to observe, to listen,

19:22.813 --> 19:25.555
and to pass on what you see.

19:25.642 --> 19:30.604
[Wolsey speaking Latin]

19:30.734 --> 19:32.910
"And He will also say
to those on his left,

19:33.041 --> 19:35.826
"'Depart from Me,
accursed ones,

19:35.957 --> 19:38.264
"'into the eternal flame

19:38.394 --> 19:41.876
which was prepared
for the Devil and his angels.'"

19:42.006 --> 19:45.140
All that is not of God,

19:45.271 --> 19:47.577
be it paper or flesh,

19:47.708 --> 19:50.363
will go to God's fire.

19:50.493 --> 19:53.279
[dramatic music]

19:53.453 --> 19:56.238
♪

20:05.291 --> 20:08.076
[indistinct chatter]

20:08.163 --> 20:10.992
♪

20:17.520 --> 20:19.522
Highness, please try to relax.

20:19.609 --> 20:21.350
You are like a wooden board.

20:21.481 --> 20:23.222
Then bathe me better,
and I will relax.

20:23.352 --> 20:24.962
[Lina chuckles]

20:25.093 --> 20:27.574
I have bathed you
for many years.

20:27.704 --> 20:30.577
No lady alive could do better.

20:30.664 --> 20:33.536
-Feel free to find one.
-I will.

20:33.667 --> 20:35.234
Immediately.

20:37.410 --> 20:38.541
[softly]
Tomorrow.

20:47.376 --> 20:49.726
Let us talk of our adventures.

20:49.857 --> 20:51.467
"Adventures"?

20:51.598 --> 20:53.904
The adventure of our lives...

20:55.645 --> 20:58.344
...when we crossed
the deserts of Castile

20:58.431 --> 21:00.346
and fought Moor rebels
and defeated them.

21:02.043 --> 21:04.959
[Lina cries softly]

21:05.089 --> 21:06.090
Why do you cry?

21:09.964 --> 21:12.967
Because those days...

21:13.054 --> 21:15.535
they were in sunlight.

21:15.665 --> 21:17.711
And now everything
is in shadow.

21:17.798 --> 21:19.713
No!

21:19.843 --> 21:22.193
No, I have
the king's love again.

21:22.324 --> 21:24.283
[Lina]
But to love the king,

21:24.370 --> 21:28.461
do you have to hate
so many others?

21:28.591 --> 21:30.680
I don't understand, Lina.

21:30.767 --> 21:33.727
[Lina]
The Lutherans.

21:33.857 --> 21:37.861
You and the cardinal
will be hanging men and women

21:37.992 --> 21:38.862
before too long.

21:38.993 --> 21:40.299
Bring me a robe.

21:40.429 --> 21:44.215
Many face ruin
and prison or worse

21:44.346 --> 21:46.392
on your command!

21:46.479 --> 21:48.698
The cardinal and I,
we are defending God, Lina.

21:48.785 --> 21:51.353
It is my duty
to defend the true faith.

21:51.484 --> 21:54.487
That was
what your mother thought.

21:54.617 --> 21:57.577
And in time,
there was Inquisición!

21:57.707 --> 22:00.057
Enough!

22:00.144 --> 22:02.756
[melancholy music]

22:02.930 --> 22:05.846
♪

22:15.682 --> 22:17.336
-Highness--
-Go! Now.

22:19.294 --> 22:22.166
♪

22:27.868 --> 22:30.000
[Henry grunts]

22:30.131 --> 22:31.480
[Brandon]
Oh, yes, good throw.

22:31.611 --> 22:33.830
-Can't be bettered.
-Eh, we'll see.

22:37.225 --> 22:39.445
[Stafford grunts,
Brandon laughing]

22:39.575 --> 22:40.359
Why?

22:47.017 --> 22:49.890
Uh, Your Majesty,
may you please excuse me?

22:50.020 --> 22:51.370
I promised my wife
I'd walk with her

22:51.457 --> 22:53.546
to see the new peacocks.

22:53.633 --> 22:55.374
Only at your pleasure,
Your Majesty.

23:03.251 --> 23:06.820
Henry,
our sister returns again.

23:06.950 --> 23:08.691
[Meg]
Hello, Catherine.

23:08.822 --> 23:09.953
Hello, brother.

23:10.084 --> 23:11.651
[grunts]

23:11.781 --> 23:13.566
My, but you do like
long rides, don't you?

23:13.696 --> 23:16.220
No, in fact, I do not.

23:16.307 --> 23:19.528
But I ride to claim
what is rightfully mine,

23:19.659 --> 23:21.617
my inheritance.

23:21.704 --> 23:23.445
Go back
to your bog-ridden country

23:23.576 --> 23:24.794
before I forget
you're my sister.

23:24.925 --> 23:26.143
Henry, please,
can we at least--

23:26.274 --> 23:28.494
[Henry]
You should be inside.

23:28.624 --> 23:31.105
The air is too chill
for my son.

23:35.065 --> 23:36.415
[Catherine]
Walk with me, Meg.

23:40.419 --> 23:44.118
It is a daily struggle
to hold my country together.

23:44.248 --> 23:46.381
I am depleted of resources.

23:46.512 --> 23:48.818
-And I demand that he honor--
-You make demands of the king?

23:48.949 --> 23:50.037
No.

23:52.431 --> 23:55.172
And as for honor,

23:55.303 --> 23:57.740
where is your honor
towards God?

23:57.871 --> 23:59.699
You defy His Majesty

23:59.829 --> 24:02.049
and ask the pope
to annul your marriage.

24:02.179 --> 24:04.138
Catherine, you once told me

24:04.268 --> 24:07.750
to fix my place in the stars
and not be diverted.

24:07.837 --> 24:11.624
I come simply
to claim what is mine.

24:11.754 --> 24:13.713
And I am fixed.

24:13.843 --> 24:16.237
What happened
to the sister I once knew?

24:16.367 --> 24:19.153
[heavy music]

24:19.240 --> 24:22.156
♪

24:23.331 --> 24:25.899
[scoffs]

24:26.029 --> 24:28.205
So we have nothing more
to discuss.

24:28.336 --> 24:29.424
Nothing.

24:29.598 --> 24:32.209
♪

24:32.340 --> 24:34.821
Farewell...

24:34.951 --> 24:36.257
Queen Margaret.

24:36.431 --> 24:39.260
♪

24:53.840 --> 24:55.145
[Hal] Are you quite certain
about this?

24:55.276 --> 24:57.321
Oh, yes, Hal Stewart.

24:57.452 --> 25:00.020
Good morning.
I trust you know who I am.

25:00.107 --> 25:01.761
Open the door.

25:01.891 --> 25:04.111
I will collect the deeds
of my inheritance.

25:04.241 --> 25:06.940
[dramatic music]

25:07.114 --> 25:10.030
♪

25:15.339 --> 25:16.906
They'll be here somewhere.

25:16.993 --> 25:19.256
To hell with parchment.

25:19.387 --> 25:21.607
I will take
what I'm owed in gold.

25:21.737 --> 25:23.478
[chuckles]

25:28.657 --> 25:30.137
Think of it as a border raid.

25:34.315 --> 25:36.056
No, Hal.

25:37.971 --> 25:38.972
Forgive me.

25:42.932 --> 25:45.935
The last man I fell for
all but ruined me.

25:47.894 --> 25:49.548
I cannot fall for another.

25:52.028 --> 25:56.293
I must remain fixed
on my course.

25:57.556 --> 25:59.253
For Scotland.

25:59.340 --> 26:02.169
♪

26:05.259 --> 26:07.957
[objects clinking]

26:09.655 --> 26:12.571
♪

26:16.444 --> 26:18.098
[Henry] Well, my sister's
a true Scot now, isn't she?

26:18.228 --> 26:19.665
As they're all thieves.

26:19.795 --> 26:22.276
You'll send riders after them?

26:22.406 --> 26:23.799
No, I will not chase after her

26:23.930 --> 26:25.845
like some commoner
robbed in the street.

26:25.975 --> 26:28.151
I will leave you, Your Majesty.

26:31.024 --> 26:34.114
Though I do hope you will think
on the other matter.

26:34.244 --> 26:35.985
Pray, what matter,
Cardinal?

26:39.336 --> 26:40.729
[Henry]
There are rumors concerning

26:40.860 --> 26:41.991
Lord Stafford.

26:44.428 --> 26:47.431
Sisters, friends--

26:47.562 --> 26:50.434
why must I waste my love
on them?

26:50.521 --> 26:52.393
You must not let
your ill humor over Meg

26:52.523 --> 26:54.221
cloud your friendship
with Edward Stafford.

26:54.351 --> 26:55.788
My power falters.

26:55.875 --> 26:57.528
The lords scoff at me.

26:57.659 --> 26:59.095
Meg robs me.

26:59.182 --> 27:01.358
Henry, your power is safe.

27:01.489 --> 27:03.926
No one can challenge that.

27:04.013 --> 27:05.536
And I am here to support you.

27:09.149 --> 27:10.803
[Ursula]
Curse the rain.

27:10.933 --> 27:14.284
I really wanted us to walk
through the gardens.

27:14.415 --> 27:17.244
The Lenten lillies and
gillyflowers are so beautiful.

27:17.374 --> 27:18.941
And the gardeners were trained
in the gardens of Richmond.

27:19.028 --> 27:21.161
It is a splendid home, Ursula.

27:21.291 --> 27:22.728
So why do you look like

27:22.815 --> 27:24.251
you've just been stung
by a bee, Lady Mother?

27:24.381 --> 27:25.556
[Maggie chuckles]

27:25.687 --> 27:28.429
I worry for all my children.

27:28.559 --> 27:31.258
It is a mother's lot,
I suppose.

27:31.388 --> 27:33.564
But Reggie is finding his way,

27:33.652 --> 27:35.610
and thanks to the kindness
of Thomas More,

27:35.741 --> 27:38.134
our Henry will find
peace of heart.

27:38.265 --> 27:40.136
You care for More.

27:40.267 --> 27:42.573
But he is married.

27:42.704 --> 27:45.446
Ursula, I do not care
for Master More in that way.

27:45.576 --> 27:47.883
Wash your mouth out.

27:48.014 --> 27:50.451
[Stafford] Ladies, enjoying
the sights of the house, I see.

27:50.581 --> 27:52.148
[Henry Stafford]
My wife is the only sight

27:52.279 --> 27:53.759
that I care for.

27:55.499 --> 27:58.111
[Ursula giggling]
Oh, Henry.

28:00.330 --> 28:02.289
-Was I ever like that?
-[chuckles]

28:02.419 --> 28:04.030
[Stafford chuckles]

28:08.469 --> 28:10.166
What's troubling you?

28:11.690 --> 28:13.648
[grunts softly]

28:13.779 --> 28:17.783
Cousin, are you concerned
about Wolsey?

28:17.913 --> 28:20.524
The butcher from Ipswich?
No, I'm not.

28:20.655 --> 28:22.222
The king likes him
because he's of common birth

28:22.352 --> 28:24.398
and cannot be a threat to him.

28:24.485 --> 28:26.617
He is now so close
to the cardinal,

28:26.748 --> 28:28.489
and we all know
what Wolsey thinks of you.

28:30.883 --> 28:32.972
My daughter is now part
of this family.

28:33.102 --> 28:34.843
[Stafford]
Ah.

28:34.930 --> 28:36.758
I see.

28:39.587 --> 28:42.633
Do not fret.

28:42.764 --> 28:45.680
I have been friends
with the king since childhood.

28:45.811 --> 28:49.205
We fought together,
drank together.

28:49.292 --> 28:52.165
We've even courted ladies
together.

28:52.252 --> 28:55.690
Let Wolsey have the king's ear.

28:55.821 --> 28:57.736
I have Henry's heart.

29:01.478 --> 29:05.091
Come, let us ride
back to Westminster...

29:07.006 --> 29:08.877
...in good spirits.

29:11.271 --> 29:13.882
[animals chattering,
insects chirping]

29:14.013 --> 29:16.972
[breathing heavily]

29:17.059 --> 29:19.714
[suspenseful music]

29:19.888 --> 29:22.761
♪

29:47.263 --> 29:49.048
[Stafford]
Take this for me.

29:49.178 --> 29:51.528
I shall retire to my rooms.

29:51.615 --> 29:54.705
[crying]
Oh...

29:54.836 --> 29:55.706
[softly]
No, no.

29:55.794 --> 29:57.143
No, no, stay away!

29:57.230 --> 29:58.405
Go!

29:58.535 --> 30:00.973
I-I'm just walking off a cramp.

30:03.062 --> 30:06.369
Ah!
[crying]

30:06.500 --> 30:09.503
[sobs, grunting]

30:09.590 --> 30:12.898
♪

30:13.028 --> 30:14.421
Your Grace?

30:14.551 --> 30:17.293
[mutters breathlessly]
Stafford, um...

30:17.424 --> 30:19.295
get me to my--

30:19.426 --> 30:21.297
Please, please take me
to my chambers, please.

30:21.428 --> 30:22.603
Your Grace, uh,
it would not be proper.

30:22.690 --> 30:23.691
Let me call your ladies--

30:23.778 --> 30:25.171
[Catherine]
Help me!

30:25.301 --> 30:26.825
[softly]
Help me, please.

30:28.870 --> 30:30.350
All right.

30:30.437 --> 30:32.308
[Catherine sobs]

30:32.439 --> 30:34.310
-All right.
-[sniffling]

30:34.441 --> 30:36.138
[Stafford]
Shh, shh, shh.

30:36.269 --> 30:38.488
Shh, shh.

30:38.575 --> 30:40.751
All right.

30:40.882 --> 30:42.188
Here.

30:42.318 --> 30:44.233
-[whimpers]
-Shh, shh, shh. Okay.

30:45.756 --> 30:48.020
[groaning]

30:48.150 --> 30:49.717
[whimpering]

30:53.503 --> 30:55.114
I-I'll call a nursemaid.

30:55.244 --> 30:57.159
No, no.

30:57.290 --> 30:59.248
Close the door.

30:59.379 --> 31:01.120
Please.

31:05.864 --> 31:06.865
[sobbing]
Why?

31:09.345 --> 31:11.260
Why can I not give him
the son he needs?

31:11.391 --> 31:13.175
Why?

31:13.306 --> 31:15.395
Is my sin so great?

31:15.525 --> 31:17.005
[whispering]
No, no, no.

31:17.136 --> 31:19.181
-Shh, shh, shh.
-[whimpering]

31:19.268 --> 31:21.880
Breathe, breathe,
breathe, breathe, breathe.

31:21.967 --> 31:23.316
You must tell no one.

31:23.446 --> 31:25.448
[gulps]
Please.

31:25.535 --> 31:26.885
[crying]
Please.

31:27.015 --> 31:29.191
Please, not the king.

31:29.278 --> 31:31.846
Please, I be--
I-I beg you.

31:31.977 --> 31:35.154
I swear to you,
I will tell no one.

31:36.764 --> 31:37.939
[whispers]
Thank you.

31:38.026 --> 31:40.899
♪

31:42.944 --> 31:45.555
[crying]

31:45.729 --> 31:48.515
♪

32:14.628 --> 32:15.934
[Stafford]
Your Grace, Your Grace.

32:18.327 --> 32:19.894
[Catherine]
Lord Stafford.

32:20.025 --> 32:21.548
If you will excuse me,

32:21.635 --> 32:23.463
the king has asked me
to eat with him.

32:23.593 --> 32:25.595
You should be resting,
Your Grace.

32:25.726 --> 32:27.423
My health is good.

32:27.554 --> 32:28.816
All is well.

32:30.687 --> 32:33.734
You may yet bear the king
a son.

32:33.864 --> 32:36.345
But if you do not,

32:36.432 --> 32:38.347
then that is God's will also.

32:41.742 --> 32:44.397
Try to find comfort
in that mystery, Your Grace.

32:44.571 --> 32:47.443
♪

33:11.337 --> 33:12.642
[Henry] I'm told
that good English people

33:12.729 --> 33:14.993
have taken heed of the warnings
you issued them.

33:15.080 --> 33:16.995
They're burning
Luther's pamphlets,

33:17.125 --> 33:19.736
punishing his followers.

33:20.955 --> 33:23.697
You and the cardinal
have done fine work for me.

33:23.784 --> 33:25.090
May I, Your Majesty?

33:25.220 --> 33:26.526
Mm.

33:32.401 --> 33:33.794
What is it?

33:36.144 --> 33:39.017
♪

33:41.715 --> 33:44.283
Very well, then.

33:44.370 --> 33:46.111
[papers rustling]

33:50.419 --> 33:52.421
What was in that paper?

33:52.595 --> 33:55.337
♪

33:55.468 --> 33:56.643
Affairs of state.

33:59.385 --> 34:01.039
You've challenged
the people of London

34:01.126 --> 34:02.736
to clean their streets
of filth.

34:04.868 --> 34:06.174
I'm cleaning
the filth at court.

34:08.002 --> 34:11.049
Will you excuse me?
I...

34:11.179 --> 34:13.007
I would like to take some air.

34:13.181 --> 34:15.966
♪

34:23.713 --> 34:25.585
[footsteps approaching]

34:28.196 --> 34:29.980
Cousin, Maggie,

34:30.111 --> 34:31.939
I would urge you
to visit the queen.

34:32.070 --> 34:33.027
She may need your help.

34:33.158 --> 34:34.202
I will.

34:34.333 --> 34:35.769
Can I ask why?

34:35.899 --> 34:37.466
[Wolsey]
Lord Stafford.

34:39.773 --> 34:41.427
[Stafford]
Wolsey.

34:41.557 --> 34:42.993
My word, you are enlisting
very ugly altar boys

34:43.124 --> 34:44.821
these days.

34:44.952 --> 34:46.736
[Wolsey] Edward Stafford,
Duke of Buckingham,

34:46.867 --> 34:48.825
you are hereby accused
of high treason against

34:48.956 --> 34:50.436
-His Majesty, King Henry...
-[Maggie] What? What possible

34:50.566 --> 34:51.741
-charge can there be...
-And the commonwealth

34:51.828 --> 34:52.916
-of England.
-Against Lord Stafford?

34:53.003 --> 34:54.266
This is pure spite.

34:54.396 --> 34:55.832
There can be no just cause

34:55.963 --> 34:57.356
against the king's
loyal friend and counselor.

34:57.443 --> 35:01.142
Do not be alarmed,
Lady Pole.

35:01.229 --> 35:05.059
The alter rex merely tests
his imagined power.

35:05.190 --> 35:08.193
Oh, but the Tower...

35:08.323 --> 35:10.108
is very...

35:10.238 --> 35:12.719
very real, my lord.

35:12.849 --> 35:15.461
[tense music]

35:15.548 --> 35:16.592
Take him away.

35:16.766 --> 35:19.552
♪

35:31.694 --> 35:34.349
Highness.

35:34.480 --> 35:35.829
Are you feeling all right?

35:35.959 --> 35:38.048
[Maggie]
Your Grace.

35:38.179 --> 35:39.441
Catherine.

35:39.528 --> 35:41.139
Maggie.

35:41.269 --> 35:42.749
Did you know
about Lord Stafford?

35:42.879 --> 35:45.665
[intense music]

35:45.752 --> 35:48.624
♪

35:50.365 --> 35:52.280
-Henry.
-[Henry] Stop.

35:52.411 --> 35:53.586
-He's a traitor.
-He is your friend.

35:53.673 --> 35:55.501
He loves you.

35:55.631 --> 35:57.155
He foolishly exploited
what he sees

35:57.285 --> 35:58.547
as a weakness in the king.

35:58.678 --> 36:00.070
A weakness
in the greatest monarch

36:00.201 --> 36:01.289
this country has ever known?

36:01.420 --> 36:03.161
-It defies reason.
-Henry.

36:05.032 --> 36:06.947
Do not throw away
those who love you.

36:07.077 --> 36:09.906
Do not upset your humors,
or you risk my son.

36:13.301 --> 36:15.303
Thomas.

36:15.434 --> 36:17.392
You are a reasonable man.

36:17.479 --> 36:19.220
Can you not make him see sense?

36:19.351 --> 36:21.527
In what fairy tale
do you suppose

36:21.657 --> 36:24.094
I would counter the king
in this matter, Your Grace?

36:24.225 --> 36:26.488
His Majesty talks of humors.

36:26.619 --> 36:28.577
Have you taken measure

36:28.708 --> 36:30.492
of the humor
at court these days?

36:30.623 --> 36:33.365
[unsettling music]

36:33.539 --> 36:36.498
♪

36:36.629 --> 36:38.326
[door closes]

36:38.457 --> 36:41.155
[bell tolling]

36:41.329 --> 36:43.940
♪

37:01.915 --> 37:03.351
Your Grace.

37:03.482 --> 37:06.006
My Lord Stafford.

37:06.093 --> 37:08.313
I have seen
some of the charges.

37:08.443 --> 37:10.228
They are absurd.

37:10.315 --> 37:12.404
You should not have
troubled yourself.

37:12.534 --> 37:14.754
I'll be here a few days.

37:14.884 --> 37:18.061
I see it clearly now.

37:18.192 --> 37:20.499
The king's mood has darkened,

37:20.629 --> 37:22.240
and the cardinal exploits him
for his own gain.

37:24.242 --> 37:26.026
But I may still reason
with Wolsey.

37:26.113 --> 37:27.549
-[scoffs]
-I believe we have

37:27.680 --> 37:29.595
a greater understanding.

37:29.725 --> 37:31.640
Henry will humiliate me,

37:31.727 --> 37:33.512
but he will not kill me.

37:33.642 --> 37:35.949
Even so...

37:36.079 --> 37:38.734
beg for the king's forgiveness.

37:38.821 --> 37:42.260
Wiltshire and Brandon
are too afraid to speak out.

37:42.390 --> 37:45.001
Promise me you will beg him.

37:45.132 --> 37:46.873
[dramatic music]

37:47.047 --> 37:48.744
♪

37:48.875 --> 37:51.051
Very well.

37:51.181 --> 37:52.879
I will beg.

37:53.053 --> 37:55.664
♪

37:55.795 --> 37:57.275
For you, my queen.

37:58.711 --> 38:01.279
[man coughing]

38:07.023 --> 38:08.982
What happened?

38:09.112 --> 38:10.418
[Stafford]
What happened?

38:10.505 --> 38:12.246
[scoffs]

38:12.333 --> 38:15.815
He's a Lutheran reformist.

38:15.945 --> 38:18.905
Racked
for his willing confession.

38:19.079 --> 38:21.908
♪

38:31.309 --> 38:33.354
[Catherine] Withdraw
your charges against Stafford.

38:36.836 --> 38:39.055
I cannot, Your Grace.

38:39.186 --> 38:40.666
-They are severe.
-He's no threat to--

38:40.796 --> 38:42.755
To the king?

38:42.885 --> 38:44.104
I believe he is.

38:45.627 --> 38:47.716
The king needs his counselors,

38:47.847 --> 38:50.110
his generals, and his friends.

38:50.240 --> 38:51.894
Stafford is all three.

38:52.025 --> 38:53.156
If you will excuse me,
Your Grace,

38:53.287 --> 38:54.419
there is a case to prepare.

38:57.944 --> 39:01.513
I thought we were allies
in the king's interest.

39:01.643 --> 39:04.733
I already have an ally
in the king's interest.

39:04.864 --> 39:06.648
[quietly]
God.

39:06.779 --> 39:09.564
And it is He who tells me

39:09.695 --> 39:12.915
that His Majesty's
greatest enemies are those...

39:13.046 --> 39:14.743
[whispering]
...closest to him.

39:17.093 --> 39:19.966
♪

39:24.492 --> 39:26.538
[maid] Master More
is finishing a letter

39:26.668 --> 39:28.801
in his study, my lady.

39:28.931 --> 39:31.543
But he says to please
find yourself at home.

39:31.673 --> 39:33.458
All rooms are open to you.

39:33.588 --> 39:35.329
Thank you.

39:35.460 --> 39:37.636
Please tell Master More
I am here on an urgent matter.

39:37.766 --> 39:39.551
I would see him
as soon as possible.

39:59.788 --> 40:02.617
[soft music]

40:02.704 --> 40:05.533
♪

40:42.744 --> 40:45.268
[dark music]

40:45.443 --> 40:48.489
♪

40:48.620 --> 40:51.231
[suspenseful music]

40:51.405 --> 40:54.321
♪

41:07.465 --> 41:10.598
[Lina] Highness,
I see you still punish me.

41:10.729 --> 41:12.557
I should dismiss you forever
for your words.

41:12.687 --> 41:14.472
[sniffles]

41:16.865 --> 41:18.998
I will give you
my deepest secrets.

41:20.652 --> 41:21.827
What secrets?

41:25.221 --> 41:28.747
My mother and father never
truly converted to Catholicism.

41:28.834 --> 41:31.880
They were Morisco.

41:32.011 --> 41:35.318
They secretly held Islam
in their hearts.

41:37.277 --> 41:39.671
There were so many like them,

41:39.758 --> 41:42.543
out of fear
for your mother's wrath.

41:42.630 --> 41:44.066
You cannot compare me
to my mother

41:44.197 --> 41:45.372
on the matter
of the Protestant.

41:45.503 --> 41:47.635
[Lina]
Can I not?

41:47.766 --> 41:50.420
Highness, you have always
craved to be your mother.

41:52.858 --> 41:55.600
If you burn books,

41:55.687 --> 41:59.386
will you soon burn people?

41:59.473 --> 42:01.780
To please your husband,

42:01.910 --> 42:04.304
will you burn other heretics?

42:04.434 --> 42:06.219
Muslims?

42:06.306 --> 42:07.742
Jews?

42:07.829 --> 42:09.309
My own husband?

42:09.439 --> 42:11.006
Of course not!

42:11.137 --> 42:13.487
All of this so that
you can be forgiven by God

42:13.618 --> 42:15.184
for marrying on a lie!

42:15.315 --> 42:18.971
He will not forgive me,
no matter how I pray.

42:19.101 --> 42:20.973
No matter what I do,

42:21.103 --> 42:23.149
God has taken
another little boy from me.

42:26.848 --> 42:29.242
I'm sorry.
I have been possessed.

42:29.372 --> 42:31.331
[Lina]
Shh.

42:36.205 --> 42:39.948
I want the sands to run upwards
in the glass, Lina.

42:43.691 --> 42:44.997
I want to go back to the days

42:45.127 --> 42:46.694
when I was so certain
of Henry's love

42:46.781 --> 42:48.435
-and of my place.
-Shh.

42:48.566 --> 42:50.742
-[sobs softly]
-I know.

42:50.872 --> 42:53.309
I know, my sweet.

42:53.440 --> 42:56.225
[dramatic music]

42:56.399 --> 42:59.185
♪

43:04.451 --> 43:05.670
[Wolsey]
Thank you, Friar.

43:07.672 --> 43:10.326
So...

43:10.457 --> 43:12.328
we have heard
that Lord Stafford

43:12.459 --> 43:14.940
consulted false prophets

43:15.070 --> 43:17.682
and necromancers

43:17.812 --> 43:20.554
to ascertain the future
of the king's reign

43:20.685 --> 43:23.122
and if he would produce
an heir.

43:23.252 --> 43:24.776
Childish gossip, Your Majesty.

43:27.169 --> 43:29.084
Lord Stafford
is a God-fearing Christian

43:29.171 --> 43:31.260
who attends Mass every day.

43:31.391 --> 43:33.045
And in France,
I believe he was the first

43:33.175 --> 43:35.525
to offer Your Majesty's
great victory at Tournai

43:35.656 --> 43:37.310
up to God.

43:37.440 --> 43:40.313
Yet, this good friar tells us

43:40.443 --> 43:44.143
that Stafford came
to the monastery at St. Tristan

43:44.273 --> 43:46.536
because he heard there was
a book that predicted

43:46.624 --> 43:48.060
the king's death.

43:48.147 --> 43:49.539
[gasps and murmurs]

43:49.670 --> 43:51.759
[Catherine] Is there
such a book, Cardinal?

43:51.890 --> 43:53.848
There is not.

43:53.935 --> 43:56.372
Ah, pity.

43:56.503 --> 44:00.072
Well, if there were, I, too,
would be intrigued to see it.

44:00.202 --> 44:02.030
[light laughter]

44:05.860 --> 44:07.470
[Wiltshire]
One of the queen's own ladies

44:07.557 --> 44:11.257
came to me with the most troubling news...

44:11.387 --> 44:14.216
that she heard Lord Stafford
with the queen, saying that--

44:18.046 --> 44:19.439
I can hardly bear
to say these words.

44:21.571 --> 44:24.270
Saying that...

44:24.400 --> 44:27.839
if the king were to never
have an heir,

44:27.969 --> 44:31.625
it would be God's judgment
upon him.

44:31.712 --> 44:33.845
He said...

44:33.975 --> 44:37.631
that if another prince
were to die,

44:37.718 --> 44:39.589
it would sit right with him.

44:39.720 --> 44:41.374
-I never said that.
-You were heard, sir!

44:41.504 --> 44:43.202
I never said that!

44:43.332 --> 44:44.986
[court murmurs]

44:45.073 --> 44:48.250
[Stafford]
I-I said that God's plans

44:48.381 --> 44:49.904
are mysterious.

44:50.035 --> 44:52.037
I was merely trying
to comfort the queen!

44:52.167 --> 44:53.212
For what?

44:53.342 --> 44:55.127
Your Majesty?

44:55.257 --> 44:56.868
Why did the queen need comfort?

45:01.263 --> 45:02.743
[Wolsey]
Were you comforting the queen

45:02.830 --> 45:04.658
when you visited
her privy chamber?

45:04.789 --> 45:06.268
[whispering voices]

45:06.355 --> 45:08.444
You-you were

45:08.575 --> 45:12.231
in the queen's
private rooms...

45:12.318 --> 45:14.494
alone...

45:14.624 --> 45:16.322
at night,

45:16.452 --> 45:18.367
were you not?

45:18.454 --> 45:20.718
[Catherine] Lord Stafford
saw that I was tired.

45:20.848 --> 45:23.155
As my ladies were not present,

45:23.242 --> 45:25.418
he escorted me
to my chambers himself.

45:25.505 --> 45:26.593
[Wolsey]
Ah.

45:26.724 --> 45:28.160
Why were your ladies absent?

45:30.728 --> 45:33.643
Stafford,
why did you not call on them?

45:33.774 --> 45:35.907
[Stafford]
Ah, because...

45:36.037 --> 45:38.910
naturally, the queen...

45:39.040 --> 45:41.347
wished to sleep undisturbed.

45:41.477 --> 45:43.262
[Wolsey]
Was it an attempt

45:43.392 --> 45:46.439
to persuade the queen on this?

45:46.569 --> 45:49.877
[court murmuring]

45:49.964 --> 45:51.749
You have been dismissive
of the king's efforts

45:51.879 --> 45:53.620
to crush the Lutheran threat.

45:53.751 --> 45:56.014
Lord Stafford
merely questioned the expense

45:56.144 --> 45:57.406
of the public purse
in quelling it.

45:57.537 --> 45:59.408
[Wolsey]
Do you see the king as cursed?

45:59.539 --> 46:00.845
[sighs]

46:00.932 --> 46:02.934
Do you, as a man

46:03.064 --> 46:06.502
with historic
family ties to York,

46:06.633 --> 46:09.854
wish to see the king
and his church

46:09.984 --> 46:11.507
overthrown?

46:11.594 --> 46:14.597
[gasps and murmurs]

46:16.512 --> 46:19.385
I love His Majesty
with all my heart.

46:19.515 --> 46:22.780
You're more than my king.
You're my friend.

46:22.867 --> 46:26.522
And my every word...

46:26.653 --> 46:28.481
a-and action

46:28.611 --> 46:31.223
is in support of him...

46:31.397 --> 46:34.095
♪

46:34.226 --> 46:36.489
...and of his queen.

46:38.317 --> 46:40.493
[softly]
Please, beg.

46:42.321 --> 46:44.192
[sighs]

46:46.760 --> 46:48.762
So I...
[clears throat]

46:48.893 --> 46:51.983
...humbly beg forgiveness

46:52.113 --> 46:55.813
for any slight or insult

46:55.943 --> 46:59.512
that I may have unwittingly...

46:59.642 --> 47:03.124
laid at His Majesty's feet.

47:03.298 --> 47:06.214
♪

47:06.345 --> 47:08.129
Henry...

47:12.264 --> 47:13.613
...forgive me.

47:13.787 --> 47:16.616
♪

47:19.662 --> 47:21.490
We have never had cause
to question your heart,

47:21.621 --> 47:24.493
Lord Stafford...

47:24.580 --> 47:27.496
and we do not now.

47:27.583 --> 47:30.412
Your service to us
has been a constant.

47:30.543 --> 47:32.675
The king has always valued
your friendship,

47:32.806 --> 47:35.374
and your contrition is full

47:35.504 --> 47:37.245
and moves us.

47:37.419 --> 47:40.248
♪

47:43.948 --> 47:46.080
[Ursula]
Did the queen save him, Mother?

47:46.211 --> 47:47.908
[Maggie]
I do not know.

47:48.039 --> 47:49.867
Oh, this wretched place,
Ursula.

47:49.997 --> 47:51.520
[More]
Lady Pole.

47:54.610 --> 47:56.482
Lady Pole, I can tell
from the look in your eye

47:56.612 --> 47:58.484
that you're in some way
displeased with me.

47:58.614 --> 48:00.051
-But I can assure you--
-Leave us, Ursula.

48:03.750 --> 48:05.970
You left my home
so suddenly, I...

48:06.057 --> 48:08.581
I could not bear
what I saw there.

48:08.711 --> 48:11.671
In your own home, Thomas...

48:11.758 --> 48:13.760
where your daughters
eat and read.

48:13.891 --> 48:15.675
[More]
Ah.

48:15.805 --> 48:18.025
When the men in that room

48:18.156 --> 48:21.507
finally confess
their rebellion, they...

48:21.637 --> 48:24.292
free themselves for salvation.

48:24.423 --> 48:26.512
I do good, Maggie.

48:26.642 --> 48:28.253
There is no good
in that machine.

48:28.383 --> 48:29.689
[More scoffs]

48:29.819 --> 48:31.691
I fight a war

48:31.778 --> 48:35.608
for God and for the Crown
every day.

48:35.738 --> 48:39.612
It is a spiritual war
against unseen forces.

48:39.742 --> 48:42.876
Yes, it is bloody, and it is...

48:43.007 --> 48:46.836
awful, and I take
no pride in it, but...

48:46.967 --> 48:51.189
it sits right
with my conscience, Maggie.

48:51.319 --> 48:54.279
How comforting
your certainty must be

48:54.409 --> 48:57.673
to raise your principles
above all men and women.

48:57.804 --> 48:59.675
How wonderful
that your conscience

48:59.806 --> 49:03.331
drowns out crying
and screaming.

49:03.462 --> 49:06.726
I will pray for such comfort
myself, Master More,

49:06.856 --> 49:09.903
for I am in great need
of some blessed peace of mind.

49:10.034 --> 49:12.732
[somber music]

49:12.906 --> 49:15.735
♪

49:20.740 --> 49:23.047
[Catherine]
Henry.

49:23.177 --> 49:25.527
If you let him die,
your heart will break.

49:25.614 --> 49:28.835
We have been fervent
in our desire to do God's will,

49:28.922 --> 49:30.837
and many have suffered for it
on the streets of London.

49:30.968 --> 49:33.579
So I wonder...

49:33.709 --> 49:36.060
if God will not bless
our fervor,

49:36.190 --> 49:39.150
then perhaps He will bless
our compassion.

49:39.280 --> 49:41.065
Why do you say this?
God has blessed us.

49:41.152 --> 49:43.110
You carry a boy.

49:43.241 --> 49:44.677
And...
[breathes shakily]

49:44.807 --> 49:46.026
...my fear for Lord Stafford

49:46.157 --> 49:48.942
may hazard our son
in the womb.

49:49.073 --> 49:50.857
Let us be temperate
with this court

49:50.988 --> 49:52.554
and this kingdom,

49:52.685 --> 49:55.253
for our son's sake...

49:55.340 --> 49:56.950
and our own.

49:57.081 --> 49:59.866
[dramatic music]

49:59.953 --> 50:02.869
♪

50:07.917 --> 50:10.833
I'll not hasten to pardon him.

50:11.008 --> 50:13.836
♪

50:29.678 --> 50:33.030
[bell tolling]

50:38.426 --> 50:41.168
[indistinct chatter]

50:41.342 --> 50:44.128
♪

50:46.347 --> 50:48.697
[thunder rumbles]

50:48.784 --> 50:50.786
[Maggie]
Ursula.

50:50.873 --> 50:54.268
The king will spare him.
The queen has said so.

50:54.399 --> 50:57.010
And your father
trusts the king.

50:57.141 --> 50:59.795
[indistinct chatter]

51:02.711 --> 51:05.671
[thunder rumbles]

51:13.200 --> 51:15.855
[indistinct chatter continues]

51:18.640 --> 51:20.033
[Brandon]
The king does not attend.

51:20.164 --> 51:21.774
The queen at least has the
courage to see this through.

51:21.861 --> 51:23.732
Shh!

51:23.819 --> 51:25.952
-[whispering] If we are heard--
-I am the king's sister.

51:26.083 --> 51:28.389
And you are Stafford's friend.

51:28.520 --> 51:30.391
Mark this day, Mary.

51:30.478 --> 51:33.220
From now on, no one is safe.

51:33.351 --> 51:35.657
[crowd murmuring]

51:39.792 --> 51:42.055
[thunder rumbling]

51:42.186 --> 51:44.840
[murmuring continues]

51:46.407 --> 51:48.670
Watch your step, my lord.

51:53.371 --> 51:56.069
[thunder rumbling]

52:05.165 --> 52:08.168
[Stafford]
Good morning, my lords.

52:08.255 --> 52:10.605
This weather
is cold and dismal.

52:12.651 --> 52:14.870
I hope today does not affect
your good health...

52:17.482 --> 52:18.831
...for it still may.

52:39.547 --> 52:42.159
[Stafford sniffs,
thunder rumbles]

52:47.816 --> 52:50.167
Edward Stafford,
Duke of Buckingham,

52:50.297 --> 52:52.560
you stand convicted of treason.

52:55.259 --> 52:58.653
You are hereby sentenced
to death.

53:00.699 --> 53:04.093
And all
your lands and titles...

53:04.224 --> 53:05.791
shall be forfeit
to the Crown...

53:07.967 --> 53:10.665
...so that your heirs
will not inherit them.

53:10.796 --> 53:13.015
The king means
to humiliate him, then?

53:13.146 --> 53:14.756
Then grant a pardon?

53:14.887 --> 53:16.802
[More]
Make way. Make way.

53:16.932 --> 53:18.673
-Your Grace.
-[Ursula] Thank God.

53:18.804 --> 53:20.588
[crowd murmuring]

53:20.675 --> 53:22.764
-A message from the king.
-Give it to me, Thomas.

53:22.851 --> 53:24.636
Your Grace,
I was ordered by the king--

53:24.723 --> 53:26.464
Give it to me!

53:26.638 --> 53:29.467
♪

53:38.171 --> 53:39.999
"To my Lord Stafford,

53:40.129 --> 53:41.870
"my dearest friend
and noble servant,

53:42.001 --> 53:43.176
I commend"--

53:43.350 --> 53:46.048
♪

53:53.882 --> 53:55.710
"I commend you this day
to Almighty God."

53:55.841 --> 53:57.886
[crowd murmurs]

53:57.973 --> 53:59.888
"I will light candles
and say prays for your soul

54:00.019 --> 54:02.761
-as it departs this world."
-[Ursula sobbing]

54:02.891 --> 54:04.284
[Catherine]
"Henry."

54:04.371 --> 54:06.721
[Ursula continues sobbing]

54:09.550 --> 54:11.857
[sobbing]

54:11.987 --> 54:14.381
[quietly]
I...

54:14.512 --> 54:17.428
hear and accept

54:17.558 --> 54:19.212
His Majesty's word.

54:19.343 --> 54:22.084
[thunder rumbles]

54:22.215 --> 54:23.260
I'm sorry.

54:23.347 --> 54:24.913
I don't have any money

54:25.000 --> 54:26.611
to pay for a clean death.

54:29.701 --> 54:32.181
The man is paid.

54:32.312 --> 54:34.532
I served you
in Tournai, sir.

54:34.619 --> 54:36.447
I serve you still.

54:38.318 --> 54:39.363
Thank you.

54:45.020 --> 54:46.413
[sobs]

54:46.587 --> 54:49.416
♪

54:52.376 --> 54:53.464
[Stafford]
My king...

54:55.727 --> 54:56.945
...my queen...

54:58.817 --> 55:01.559
...I love you both.

55:01.689 --> 55:02.995
I never wished you any harm.

55:05.650 --> 55:10.089
My last act upon this earth
is to offer a prayer

55:10.219 --> 55:13.919
for your long
and happy reign...

55:16.269 --> 55:17.923
...and to wish you a son.

55:19.577 --> 55:22.841
[voice breaking]
With all my heart,

55:22.928 --> 55:24.103
a son.

55:25.017 --> 55:27.889
[thunder rumbling]

55:28.020 --> 55:30.327
[softly]
Vivat rex.

55:32.503 --> 55:34.418
[normal voice]
Long live the king.

55:34.548 --> 55:36.202
[all]
Long live the king.

55:36.289 --> 55:37.856
Fuck off.

55:38.030 --> 55:40.859
♪

55:58.442 --> 56:00.095
[chuckles softly]

56:01.532 --> 56:05.318
[crowd gasping, murmuring]

56:16.851 --> 56:18.592
[Ursula sobbing]

56:22.030 --> 56:24.032
Long live the king.

56:24.119 --> 56:26.513
[all]
Long live the king.

56:26.687 --> 56:29.516
♪

56:40.875 --> 56:42.790
Your Grace,

56:42.921 --> 56:45.793
the king is exhausted.

56:48.579 --> 56:50.711
I am surprised
you do not curl up to sleep

56:50.842 --> 56:53.366
-at the foot of his bed.
-[chuckles derisively]

56:53.497 --> 56:55.542
I will speak with him
at first light.

56:55.673 --> 56:57.370
[Wolsey] His Majesty
leaves early to hunt.

56:57.544 --> 56:59.981
♪

57:00.112 --> 57:03.245
Are you happy, Wolsey?

57:03.332 --> 57:05.770
You have your place
by the fire,

57:05.857 --> 57:08.425
but I wonder how warm
it may become for you in time.

57:10.818 --> 57:12.385
Your Grace?

57:12.516 --> 57:15.083
If Henry seeks the annulment
of our marriage,

57:15.214 --> 57:17.172
the pope will consult
the Holy Roman Emperor,

57:17.259 --> 57:20.567
who is my nephew Charles.

57:20.698 --> 57:22.526
And Charles will tell him
that I'm Henry's wife

57:22.656 --> 57:24.702
in God's eyes and the law.

57:24.832 --> 57:27.052
And nothing on this earth
can change that.

57:29.010 --> 57:30.708
Who will you side with then,

57:30.838 --> 57:33.537
Cardinal?

57:33.667 --> 57:35.495
Your God and pope
or your king?

57:36.975 --> 57:38.629
I suggest you pray on it.

57:41.196 --> 57:45.723
[Wolsey]
I do fear sometimes that...

57:45.853 --> 57:48.073
the fire is warm.

57:48.247 --> 57:51.076
♪

57:51.206 --> 57:53.731
What secret will burn you,

57:53.861 --> 57:55.080
Your Grace?

57:55.254 --> 57:58.126
♪

58:02.391 --> 58:05.090
[heavy music]

58:05.264 --> 58:08.180
♪

58:10.312 --> 58:12.880
[dramatic singing in Spanish]

58:13.054 --> 58:15.883
♪
